output:
I will arise and go now, and go to Inishfree,
On the small cabin build there, of clay and wattle's mace.
Nine bean rows will I have there, a hive for the honeybee,
And live alone in the beelow clay.
And I shall have some peace there, where peace comes dropping slow,
Dropping from the days of the morning to where the cricket sings.
There midnights all a-glimmer, a noon of purple glow,
And evening full of the lemon-sea waves.
On the small cabin build there, of clay and wattle's mace.
I will arise and go now, but always night and day,
I hear lake water lapping, with low sounds by the shore,
While I stand on the roadway, or on the pavement's grave,
I hear it, I hear it in the deep heart's hole.
